task.summary: Got this to work in Shotgun. Had to move it to manual, and shift a few folders around.
Got the save and select HDRIs to work
Setting up siouxsie to run a proper worker thread with progress bar
Well, ok. So this kills Maya every time. I think it has to do with the save functions. I'l look into it later

So, after setting up some buffers for the Thread, I'm starting to think that the external processor may not be the best idea for a shotgun tool running inside Maya. I'm going to revert to the pre-threaded version and get it to work that way.
Removed the threaded features. Going back to the orginal single process version. I'll update the UI as the processes go along, and then hope that it works.
Have the camera and new file creation working. Added configuration for the task name
Beginning to add in the HDRI and render layers. Figuring out the Arnold setup. Needs connection to the default illumination shit.
Beginning to setup the render layers.
HDRI overrides are working for all layers. Need to figure out how to turn off the default layer, set individual light overrides and then add all the other render setups.
Made some, but bad progress on the light setup.
Updated UI with chrome and mirror balls. Disabled the Scene Lights option. Set goals for the next steps toward completion
